  </div>
</section>

<!-- ─── CHARACTERS ─── -->
<section id="characters">
  <div class="characters-header reveal">
    <p class="section-label">The Players</p>
    <h2 class="section-headline">Men of shadow.<br>A daughter of truth.</h2>
  </div>

  <div class="char-grid">

    <div class="char-card reveal">
      <div class="char-number">01</div>
      <span class="char-role-badge">Protagonist · Crime Lord</span>
      <h3 class="char-name">Raghav</h3>
      <p class="char-subtitle">The King Who Forgot He Had a Son</p>
      <div class="char-divider"></div>
      <p class="char-desc">Steel-gray hair, a scar near his left brow, and a name that once silenced rooms. Raghav built a ghost empire on fire and silence. He abandoned a woman and child in the slums decades ago — believing money could buy absolution. Now that abandoned son has come to collect.</p>
      <div class="char-traits">
        <span class="char-trait">Ruthless</span>
        <span class="char-trait">Calculating</span>
        <span class="char-trait">Haunted by Guilt</span>
        <span class="char-trait">Fiercely Protective</span>
        <span class="char-trait">Old-School</span>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="char-card reveal" style="transition-delay:0.1s;">
      <div class="char-number">02</div>
      <span class="char-role-badge">Protagonist · Former Assassin</span>
      <h3 class="char-name">Veer</h3>
      <p class="char-subtitle">"The Fox" — A Ghost Who Chose Peace</p>
      <div class="char-divider"></div>
      <p class="char-desc">Known internationally as The Fox, Veer was a black-ops operative who burned six arms deals in Ukraine before vanishing. He chose peace when he chose Aaradhya. But peace refuses to be permanent — because the same boy he once spared in a warzone is now the Phantom hunting them all.</p>
      <div class="char-traits">
        <span class="char-trait">Lethal Precision</span>
        <span class="char-trait">Emotionally Restrained</span>
        <span class="char-trait">Loyal</span>
        <span class="char-trait">Conflicted</span>
        <span class="char-trait">Protective</span>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="char-card reveal" style="transition-delay:0.2s;">
      <div class="char-number">03</div>
      <span class="char-role-badge">Antagonist · The Phantom</span>
      <h3 class="char-name">Aryan</h3>
      <p class="char-subtitle">The Son the Empire Created</p>
      <div class="char-divider"></div>
      <p class="char-desc">Half-burned face. Eyes full of defiance. Aryan is what Raghav's abandonment made — a man weaponized by rage, trained by shadows, and driven by a need to burn everything his father touched. He is the ghost Raghav never stopped fearing. And Aaradhya's blood brother.</p>
      <div class="char-traits">
        <span class="char-trait">Vengeful</span>
        <span class="char-trait">Brilliant</span>
        <span class="char-trait">Broken</span>
        <span class="char-trait">Manipulative</span>
        <span class="char-trait">Tragically Human</span>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="char-card reveal" style="transition-delay:0.3s;">
      <div class="char-number">04</div>
      <span class="char-role-badge">Central Character · The Truth-Seeker</span>
      <h3 class="char-name">Aaradhya</h3>
      <p class="char-subtitle">Daughter. Wife. The Only Honest One Left.</p>
      <div class="char-divider"></div>
      <p class="char-desc">Raghav's beloved daughter, Veer's wife, and Aryan's half-sister — though she discovers each of these truths at the worst possible moment. Aaradhya is not a bystander. She is the moral heart of the story, choosing truth over blood when every man around her chooses war.</p>
      <div class="char-traits">
        <span class="char-trait">Perceptive</span>
        <span class="char-trait">Courageous</span>
        <span class="char-trait">Emotionally Complex</span>
        <span class="char-trait">Principled</span>
        <span class="char-trait">Decisive</span>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="char-card reveal" style="transition-delay:0.4s;">
      <div class="char-number">05</div>
      <span class="char-role-badge">Ghost · The True Wildcard</span>
      <h3 class="char-name">Meenakshi</h3>
      <p class="char-subtitle">The Mother Who Never Died</p>
      <div class="char-divider"></div>
      <p class="char-desc">Officially dead for over 20 years. Raghav's first love, Aryan's mother, Aaradhya's biological mother. Her journals reveal a woman who loved deeply and sacrificed everything. But the epilogue reveals something terrifying: she survived — and she's been watching. Now she's coming for everyone.</p>
      <div class="char-traits">
        <span class="char-trait">Mysterious</span>
        <span class="char-trait">Quietly Dangerous</span>
        <span class="char-trait">Wounded</span>
        <span class="char-trait">Strategic</span>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="char-card reveal" style="transition-delay:0.5s;">
      <div class="char-number">06</div>
      <span class="char-role-badge">Supporting · Traitor Within</span>
      <h3 class="char-name">Hari</h3>
      <p class="char-subtitle">The Loyalist Who Chose the Other Son</p>
      <div class="char-divider"></div>
      <p class="char-desc">Raghav's advisor of 18 years. He held Aaradhya as a baby, lit temple lamps every Diwali — and fed Aryan information for years. His betrayal is not simply treachery: it is the moral judgment of a man who believed Raghav's abandoned son deserved the kingdom more than his master.</p>
      <div class="char-traits">
        <span class="char-trait">Secretly Principled</span>
        <span class="char-trait">Resentful</span>
        <span class="char-trait">Brave in Defeat</span>
      </div>
    </div>

  </div>
</section>

<!-- ─── CHAPTERS ─── -->
<section id="chapters">
  <div class="chapters-header reveal">
    <p class="section-label">The Structure</p>
    <h2 class="section-headline">Thirteen acts of fire and reckoning</h2>
  </div>

  <div class="chapters-grid">

    <div class="chapter-card reveal">
      <a href="https://www.inkitt.com/stories/1506702/chapters/1" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="chapter-card-link">
        <div class="chapter-num">Chapter I</div>
        <h3 class="chapter-title">Ashes in the Wind</h3>
        <p class="chapter-epigraph">"Your sins will return, bhai. Not to you — but to your daughter."</p>
        <p class="chapter-teaser">Three of Raghav's properties burn in a single week. His empire is being dismantled by someone who knows too much. A mysterious video message arrives: "CHECKMATE BEGINS. PHASE ONE." The city is afraid. And the silence that was once Raghav's weapon... is no longer his.</p>
      </a>
    </div>

    <div class="chapter-card reveal" style="transition-delay:0.05s;">
      <a href="https://www.inkitt.com/stories/1506702/chapters/2" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="chapter-card-link">
        <div class="chapter-num">Chapter II</div>
        <h3 class="chapter-title">Faces of Peace</h3>
        <p class="chapter-epigraph">"You don't always see a storm coming. Sometimes it hides in a smile."</p>
        <p class="chapter-teaser">A rooftop dinner. A father-in-law who is something more than a businessman. Veer's trained eyes scan every exit, every suspicious waiter. Then Aaradhya excuses herself to the washroom — and doesn't come back. The wolves are no longer watching. They've already moved.</p>
      </a>
    </div>

    <div class="chapter-card reveal" style="transition-delay:0.1s;">
      <a href="https://www.inkitt.com/stories/1506702/chapters/3" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="chapter-card-link">
        <div class="chapter-num">Chapter III</div>
        <h3 class="chapter-title">The Phantom Emerges</h3>
        <p class="chapter-epigraph">"The worst enemies are the ones you don't remember creating — until they come wearing your own face."</p>
        <p class="chapter-teaser">A name surfaces from the underworld: Phantom. A surviving attacker whispers it in terror. Raghav opens a locked envelope containing a faded photo and old documents. The truth about a slum, a woman, and a child he abandoned rises from 20 years of repression.</p>
      </a>
    </div>

    <div class="chapter-card reveal" style="transition-delay:0.15s;">
      <a href="https://www.inkitt.com/stories/1506702/chapters/4" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="chapter-card-link">
        <div class="chapter-num">Chapter IV</div>
        <h3 class="chapter-title">Dual Pasts</h3>
        <p class="chapter-epigraph">"The blood we're born from doesn't define us. The choices we make with it do."</p>
        <p class="chapter-teaser">Two men. Two buried histories. Veer's classified past as The Fox — a ghost of Eastern European shadow wars — begins to unravel. Aryan is revealed to be no accident: he was trained, weaponized, and pointed at Raghav like a loaded gun. And Aaradhya finds the secret drawer.</p>
      </a>
    </div>

    <div class="chapter-card reveal" style="transition-delay:0.2s;">
      <a href="https://www.inkitt.com/stories/1506702/chapters/5" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="chapter-card-link">
        <div class="chapter-num">Chapter V</div>
        <h3 class="chapter-title">Fractures</h3>
        <p class="chapter-epigraph">"Sometimes the most painful wounds are not from bullets, but from truth."</p>
        <p class="chapter-teaser">The estate is breached in an audacious night attack — a test of Raghav and Veer's defences. Inside, the marriage fractures. Aaradhya receives a video call from an unknown brother. She meets Aryan in an abandoned metro station, and the music box she's carried since childhood plays its real origin.</p>
      </a>
    </div>

    <div class="chapter-card reveal" style="transition-delay:0.25s;">
      <a href="https://www.inkitt.com/stories/1506702/chapters/6" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="chapter-card-link">
        <div class="chapter-num">Chapter VI</div>
        <h3 class="chapter-title">Blood Will Speak</h3>
        <p class="chapter-epigraph">"It's not always bullets that pierce the heart. Sometimes, it's truth — or something that looks like it."</p>
        <p class="chapter-teaser">Aaradhya is taken — gently — to Aryan's compound. He shows her fabricated evidence placing Veer at the site of her mother's disappearance. Meanwhile, Veer activates an outlawed surveillance program and follows a heat signature deep into the mountains. The truth is fragile. The lie is perfect.</p>
      </a>
    </div>

    <div class="chapter-card reveal" style="transition-delay:0.3s;">
      <a href="https://www.inkitt.com/stories/1506702/chapters/7" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="chapter-card-link">
        <div class="chapter-num">Chapter VII</div>
        <h3 class="chapter-title">Ghost Protocol</h3>
        <p class="chapter-epigraph">"The ghosts we bury always come back wearing familiar faces."</p>
        <p class="chapter-teaser">Veer travels to Istanbul, confronting a man from his past war life. A flashback reveals that the boy he once spared on a Syrian battlefield in 2011 — the boy with the broken conch pendant — was Aryan himself. Inside the estate, a trusted man fires a sniper round into Raghav's shoulder. The mole is real.</p>
      </a>
    </div>

    <div class="chapter-card reveal" style="transition-delay:0.35s;">
      <a href="https://www.inkitt.com/stories/1506702/chapters/8" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="chapter-card-link">
        <div class="chapter-num">Chapter VIII</div>
        <h3 class="chapter-title">The Mole</h3>
        <p class="chapter-epigraph">"The deepest cuts don't come from knives. They come from people you trust."</p>
        <p class="chapter-teaser">Hari — 18 years at Raghav's side — is dragged to the basement. Veer's interrogation is methodical and brutal, and Aaradhya watches it on a hacked feed. Hari's confession reveals that Aryan doesn't want to destroy the empire. He wants to replace it. And Aaradhya breaks.</p>
      </a>
    </div>

    <div class="chapter-card reveal" style="transition-delay:0.4s;">
      <a href="https://www.inkitt.com/stories/1506702/chapters/9" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="chapter-card-link">
        <div class="chapter-num">Chapter IX</div>
        <h3 class="chapter-title">Death Trade</h3>
        <p class="chapter-epigraph">"When kings fall, thieves become emperors."</p>
        <p class="chapter-teaser">Aryan unleashes Phase 3. He leaks Veer's classified kill files and Raghav's corrupted past to global media simultaneously. The empire collapses overnight. Rival factions claim the streets. Veer destroys a six-truck weapons convoy single-handedly on a highway. And one bomb falls thirty seconds early.</p>
      </a>
    </div>

    <div class="chapter-card reveal" style="transition-delay:0.43s;">
      <a href="https://www.inkitt.com/stories/1506702/chapters/10" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="chapter-card-link">
        <div class="chapter-num">Chapter X</div>
        <h3 class="chapter-title">The Widow Files</h3>
        <p class="chapter-epigraph">"Some stories are buried, not because they're lies, but because they're too true to survive."</p>
        <p class="chapter-teaser">Unable to sleep in the quiet compound, Aaradhya discovers her mother Meenakshi's hidden leather-bound journal from 2004-2006 inside Aryan's private safe. The handwritten pages reveal a heartbreaking reality: Meenakshi left not because she was abandoned, but to protect her children from Raghav's rising enemies. Aryan's engineered narrative instantly shatters.</p>
      </a>
    </div>

    <div class="chapter-card reveal" style="transition-delay:0.45s;">
      <a href="https://www.inkitt.com/stories/1506702/chapters/11" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="chapter-card-link">
        <div class="chapter-num">Chapter XI</div>
        <h3 class="chapter-title">City of Ashes</h3>
        <p class="chapter-epigraph">"When the fire you set to destroy monsters ends up consuming angels, you've already become what you hated."</p>
        <p class="chapter-teaser">Aryan targets Raghav's final infrastructure hubs, but a data transmission error triggers an explosion early at Dharavi Slum Zone 8. St. Anselm's School burns down, killing twenty-five innocent children. Public sentiment backfires brutally; leaked internal war-room data labels Aryan a domestic war criminal, fracturing his remaining alliance lines.</p>
      </a>
    </div>

    <div class="chapter-card reveal" style="transition-delay:0.47s;">
      <a href="https://www.inkitt.com/stories/1506702/chapters/12" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="chapter-card-link">
        <div class="chapter-num">Chapter XII</div>
        <h3 class="chapter-title">Bloodlines Collide</h3>
        <p class="chapter-epigraph">"Blood makes you related. Loyalty makes you deadly."</p>
        <p class="chapter-teaser">Aryan launches an EMP ambush on Safehouse Alpha, capturing Veer and Raghav. Inside an atomic-era bunker in the Aravalli hills, a profound psychological duel unfolds. Veer breaks the ultimate truth to Aryan: he was the legendary shadow black-ops soldier who explicitly chose to spare a starving twelve-year-old child's life in Syria back in 2011.</p>
      </a>
    </div>

    <div class="chapter-card reveal" style="transition-delay:0.5s;">
      <a href="https://www.inkitt.com/stories/1506702/chapters/13" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="chapter-card-link">
        <div class="chapter-num">Chapter XIII</div>
        <h3 class="chapter-title">Queen's Choice</h3>
        <p class="chapter-epigraph">"In a family torn by war, the one who sees both sides must decide whether to unite or destroy."</p>
        <p class="chapter-teaser">Aaradhya crushes Veer's blackmail files under her heel, logs a satellite signal, and escapes Aryan's base via a hidden service shaft mapped by Veer. Reunited with an injured, escaped Veer and an aging Raghav at a mountain hideout, she rejects choosing between bloodlines. Raghav hands her the keys to his final absolute truth vault.</p>
      </a>
    </div>

    <div class="chapter-card reveal" style="transition-delay:0.55s;">
      <a href="https://www.inkitt.com/stories/1506702/chapters/14" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="chapter-card-link">
        <div class="chapter-num">Finale</div>
        <h3 class="chapter-title">Happy Father's Day</h3>
        <p class="chapter-epigraph">"A legacy built in blood must end in silence."</p>
        <p class="chapter-teaser">At 4:27 AM in Chennai, the definitive collision happens. To guarantee safety for Veer and Aaradhya, Raghav triggers an untraceable heart-stop mechanism on his wrist to fake his public demise while Aryan face-off fires. Months later, a secure stream confirms Raghav is alive as a nameless wanderer. In prison, Aryan receives an unannounced visit from his father.</p>
      </a>
    </div>

  </div>
</section>

<!-- ─── QUOTES ─── -->
<section id="quotes">
  <div style="max-width:1200px;margin:0 auto;">
    <div class="reveal" style="margin-bottom:4rem;">
      <p class="section-label">Lines That Burn</p>
      <h2 class="section-headline">Words cut from shadow</h2>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="featured-quote-wrap reveal">
    <p class="featured-quote-text">
      "I married you because it was the first thing I did that wasn't a mission."
    </p>
    <p class="featured-quote-attr">— Veer to Aaradhya, Chapter IV</p>
  </div>

  <div class="quotes-grid">

    <div class="quote-card reveal">
      <span class="quote-mark">"</span>
      <p class="quote-text">He walks among them like nothing happened. He thinks he's clean.</p>
      <p class="quote-attr">— Aryan, watching Veer from the shadows</p>
    </div>

    <div class="quote-card reveal" style="transition-delay:0.1s;">
      <span class="quote-mark">"</span>
      <p class="quote-text">All your sins will come for your daughter someday. That's how the universe works. You may be powerful... but karma never forgets, bhai.</p>
      <p class="quote-attr">— Slum woman's prophecy to Raghav</p>
    </div>

    <div class="quote-card reveal" style="transition-delay:0.2s;">
      <span class="quote-mark">"</span>
      <p class="quote-text">Your sins have children now.</p>
      <p class="quote-attr">— Aryan, first message to Raghav</p>
    </div>

    <div class="quote-card reveal" style="transition-delay:0.3s;">
      <span class="quote-mark">"</span>
      <p class="quote-text">You can die hating him. Or live accepting that he still loves you.</p>
      <p class="quote-attr">— Veer to Aryan, inside the burning bunker</p>
    </div>

    <div class="quote-card reveal" style="transition-delay:0.4s;">
      <span class="quote-mark">"</span>
      <p class="quote-text">I loved her so much I let her go. That was the first time I died.</p>
      <p class="quote-attr">— Raghav to Aaradhya, on Meenakshi</p>
    </div>

    <div class="quote-card reveal" style="transition-delay:0.5s;">
      <span class="quote-mark">"</span>
      <p class="quote-text">He's not evil, Aaradhya. He's just been at war too long.</p>
      <p class="quote-attr">— Aryan, on Veer</p>
    </div>

    <div class="quote-card reveal" style="transition-delay:0.6s;">
      <span class="quote-mark">"</span>
      <p class="quote-text">I'm not afraid of dying. I'm afraid of becoming you.</p>
      <p class="quote-attr">— Hari, to Veer during interrogation</p>
    </div>

    <div class="quote-card reveal" style="transition-delay:0.7s;">
      <span class="quote-mark">"</span>
      <p class="quote-text">Redemption isn't always earned through penance. Sometimes it's earned through silence.</p>
      <p class="quote-attr">— Raghav's final video message</p>
    </div>

    <div class="quote-card reveal" style="transition-delay:0.8s;">
      <span class="quote-mark">"</span>
      <p class="quote-text">Tomorrow... I don't choose a side. I choose what this family becomes.</p>
      <p class="quote-attr">— Aaradhya, the night before the final battle</p>
    </div>

  </div>
</section>

<!-- ─── JOURNEY ─── -->
<section id="journey">
  <div class="journey-header reveal">
    <p class="section-label">The Arc</p>
    <h2 class="section-headline">From empire to ashes — and silence beyond</h2>
  </div>

  <div class="timeline">

    <div class="timeline-item">
      <div class="timeline-marker">
        <div class="marker-dot"></div>
        <div class="marker-num">01</div>
      </div>
      <div class="timeline-content">
        <p class="timeline-phase">The Kingdom Burns</p>
        <h3 class="timeline-event">Checkmate Begins</h3>
        <p class="timeline-desc">Raghav's untraceable assets vanish one by one in coordinated fires. A video message plays — a black king falls — and four words appear: <em>Checkmate Begins. Phase One.</em> The empire that once silenced cities is now the prey.</p>
        <p class="timeline-quote">"They're not looking for my empire. They already know where it is."</p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="timeline-item">
      <div class="timeline-marker">
        <div class="marker-dot"></div>
        <div class="marker-num">02</div>
      </div>
      <div class="timeline-content">
        <p class="timeline-phase">First Strike</p>
        <h3 class="timeline-event">Aaradhya Is Taken</h3>
        <p class="timeline-desc">At a rooftop restaurant, while father and son-in-law observe each other over dinner, Aaradhya is abducted through a staged kitchen encounter. A live video of her bound and terrified plays on Raghav's phone. Both men awaken into their old selves.</p>
        <p class="timeline-quote">"Let's make them regret waking it."</p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="timeline-item">
      <div class="timeline-marker">
        <div class="marker-dot"></div>
        <div class="marker-num">03</div>
      </div>
      <div class="timeline-content">
        <p class="timeline-phase">The Past Surfaces</p>
        <h3 class="timeline-event">A Son Raghav Abandoned</h3>
        <p class="timeline-desc">The name Phantom surfaces. Raghav reveals his secret: decades ago he fathered a child with a slum woman, left money, told her to disappear, and returned too late. That boy — Aryan — was taken, sold, and forged into something unrecognizable by the world's cruelty.</p>
        <p class="timeline-quote">"I didn't forget them. But years passed. And then Aaradhya was born."</p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="timeline-item">
      <div class="timeline-marker">
        <div class="marker-dot"></div>
        <div class="marker-num">04</div>
      </div>
      <div class="timeline-content">
        <p class="timeline-phase">Fracture Lines</p>
        <h3 class="timeline-event">Aaradhya Meets Her Brother</h3>
        <p class="timeline-desc">In an abandoned metro station, Aaradhya meets Aryan unmasked. He hands her a music box — a childhood heirloom she thought was from her father. It was from him. The foundations of her identity begin to crack, as does her trust in both Veer and Raghav.</p>
        <p class="timeline-quote">"You're not lying, are you?" "No. But he is."</p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="timeline-item">
      <div class="timeline-marker">
        <div class="marker-dot"></div>
        <div class="marker-num">05</div>
      </div>
      <div class="timeline-content">
        <p class="timeline-phase">The Widow Files</p>
        <h3 class="timeline-event">Meenakshi's Journal</h3>
        <p class="timeline-desc">Aaradhya finds her mother's private journal hidden in Aryan's safe. The pages reveal a woman who loved Raghav deeply — who left not because she was abandoned, but to protect her child from his enemies. Aryan's version of events begins to crumble.</p>
        <p class="timeline-quote">"I vanished because I loved too much."</p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="timeline-item">
      <div class="timeline-marker">
        <div class="marker-dot"></div>
        <div class="marker-num">06</div>
      </div>
      <div class="timeline-content">
        <p class="timeline-phase">City of Ashes</p>
        <h3 class="timeline-event">The School</h3>
        <p class="timeline-desc">Aryan detonates coordinated bombs across Mumbai to destroy Raghav's final infrastructure. But one bomb triggers early. St. Anselm's School for Underprivileged Children burns. Twenty-five children die. Aryan's revolution becomes a massacre — and the world turns on the Phantom.</p>
        <p class="timeline-quote">"You were supposed to save children, Aryan. Not bury them."</p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="timeline-item">
      <div class="timeline-marker">
        <div class="marker-dot"></div>
        <div class="marker-num">07</div>
      </div>
      <div class="timeline-content">
        <p class="timeline-phase">The Bunker</p>
        <h3 class="timeline-event">Two Men. One Truth.</h3>
        <p class="timeline-desc">Aryan captures Veer and Raghav. In a Cold War bunker set to detonate, the two adversaries finally face each other without masks. Veer reveals he was the soldier who spared a starving boy on a Syrian battlefield in 2011. That boy was Aryan. And he would spare him again.</p>
        <p class="timeline-quote">"So you could become more than him — not worse than him!"</p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="timeline-item">
      <div class="timeline-marker">
        <div class="marker-dot"></div>
        <div class="marker-num">08</div>
      </div>
      <div class="timeline-content">
        <p class="timeline-phase">The Final Day</p>
        <h3 class="timeline-event">Happy Father's Day</h3>
        <p class="timeline-desc">At 4:27 AM in Chennai, the final collision. Raghav stages his own death to give those he loves their freedom. Aryan is arrested. Veer and Aaradhya disappear into a hillside life of healing and silence. And months later, a secure video plays — Raghav, alive, by a lake.</p>
        <p class="timeline-quote">"Tell her I love her. But don't let her come looking."</p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="timeline-item">
      <div class="timeline-marker">
        <div class="marker-dot" style="background:var(--ember);border-color:var(--ember);box-shadow:0 0 16px rgba(224,92,42,0.7);"></div>
        <div class="marker-num">EP</div>
      </div>
      <div class="timeline-content">
        <p class="timeline-phase">Epilogue — The Echo</p>
        <h3 class="timeline-event">A Mother Returns</h3>
        <p class="timeline-desc">Years later. Peace. A neem tree. Children. Aaradhya reading her mother's restored journal under open sky. But at the Indo-Nepal border, under cover of 3:03 AM, a woman steps from a black convoy. Graceful. Hollow-eyed. Officially dead for twenty years. Meenakshi is alive — and coming for everything.</p>
        <p class="timeline-quote">"They wanted ghosts? Let them have one."</p>
      </div>
    </div>

  </div>
</section>

<!-- ─── ENDING ─── -->
<section id="ending">
  <div class="ending-content">
    <p class="section-label" style="justify-content:center;margin-bottom:3rem;">The Final Word</p>
    <h2 class="ending-message">
      Peace is paid for in <em>blood</em>.<br>
      And silence is how the guilty love.
    </h2>
    <p class="ending-quote">
      "He let me rot. She forgot me. And he took my son."
    </p>
    <p class="ending-attr">— Meenakshi, the ghost none of them expected</p>
    <p class="ending-reflection">
      Happy Father's Day is not a story about villains and heroes. It is a story about the weight a father carries when he chooses power over love — and what grows in the wound he leaves behind. Raghav's silence was his sin. Aryan's rage was his inheritance. And Aaradhya's strength was the story's only real redemption.
    </p>
    <p class="ending-reflection" style="margin-bottom:0;">
      The final image — a man by a lake, face unseen, casting a line into still water — is not closure. It is the question every flawed father asks at the end: <em>Was any of it enough?</em>
    </p>
    <br><br>
    <div class="ending-emblem"></div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- ─── FOOTER ─── -->
<footer>
  <div>
    <div class="footer-title">Happy Father's Day</div>
    <div class="footer-author">Written by Deva Harsha V</div>
  </div>
  <div class="footer-center">
    <div class="footer-divider"></div>
    <p class="footer-quote">"Some stories don't end. They just stop speaking."</p>
  </div>
  <div class="footer-right">
    A Story of Blood &amp; Silence
  </div>
</footer>

<script>
  // Advanced Viewport Element Intersection Tracker
  const nav = document.getElementById('mainNav');
  const storySection = document.getElementById('story');

  window.addEventListener('scroll', () => {
    if (storySection) {
      // Calculate active pixel tracking position dynamically relative to window bounds
      const storyTopPosition = storySection.getBoundingClientRect().top;
      
      // Trigger navigation menu dropdown transition exactly when "The Story" passes top-row threshold
      if (storyTopPosition <= 64) {
        nav.classList.add('scrolled');
      } else {
        nav.classList.remove('scrolled');
      }
    }
  });

  // Scroll reveal framework
  const revealEls = document.querySelectorAll('.reveal');
  const observer = new IntersectionObserver((entries) => {
    entries.forEach(e => {
      if (e.isIntersecting) {
        e.target.classList.add('visible');
      }
    });
  }, { threshold: 0.12 });
  revealEls.forEach(el => observer.observe(el));

  // Timeline item stagger handler
  const timelineItems = document.querySelectorAll('.timeline-item');
  const tlObserver = new IntersectionObserver((entries) => {
    entries.forEach((e, i) => {
      if (e.isIntersecting) {
        setTimeout(() => e.target.classList.add('visible'), i * 100);
      }
    });
  }, { threshold: 0.1 });
  timelineItems.forEach(el => tlObserver.observe(el));

  // Premium cinematic fluid text drop effect
  setTimeout(() => {
    const drip = document.querySelector('.blood-drip');
    if (drip) drip.style.setProperty('--drip-active', '1');
  }, 2000);
</script>
<%- include('partials/footer') %>